h": "642a8d60d51b748cc8d203d8b27d87345cdd0456740e0b1e6e76be52f3fba768", "ref_doc_id": "68af4cc8-3e54-4d69-a58a-92d81c3d9720"}, "df746b5e-e03e-41f5-bea3-65fbea3e9bcd": {"doc_hash": "2aa7079e47ae0c835c102a5c79ee0515f71948f828790fe83777203d15fff0aa", "ref_doc_id": "68af4cc8-3e54-4d69-a58a-92d81c3d9720"}, "6effce94-61de-4d8e-b3bc-c016ee09f5c0": {"doc_hash": "eb84cfde302180b52eb5bd330837546c1bd0c9a8780302a004f49b7e0dcf1113", "ref_doc_id": "68af4cc8-3e54-4d69-a58a-92d81c3d9720"}}, "docstore/data": {"07252161-1314-488a-8062-031ebdc040e1": {"__data__": {"id_": "07252161-1314-488a-8062-031ebdc040e1", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "next_section_summary": "The section emphasizes the importance of viewing meetings with members as opportunities to strengthen democratic processes within the organization and foster community relationships. It highlights the need to go beyond legal requirements and focus on creating spaces for self-reflection, critique, and collective power. The section also mentions resources from the Comit\u00e9 sectoriel de main-d\u2019\u0153uvre (CSMO) and an article on making AGMs more engaging and impactful.", "section_summary": "This section covers the importance of Annual General Meetings and Special General Meetings for non-profit organizations. It emphasizes the legal obligations for holding these meetings but also highlights the significance of these gatherings in strengthening democratic processes within the organization and allowing members to have a say in important decisions. The section also mentions the role of meetings in fostering relationships and providing space for self-reflection within community groups.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How does the document emphasize the importance of Annual General Meetings and Special General Meetings for non-profit organizations beyond just legal obligations?\n2. What resources are mentioned in the section for creating engaging and impactful Annual General Meetings?\n3. How does the document suggest that meetings with members can be used to strengthen democratic processes within an organization and foster community relationships?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "c631f355-dd41-4a54-9a7e-7aa87c241786", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "55650bb8e4a595e342832c93108c642e108f4e2b23093ef72e456a7b9a843e77", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "94cfbd58-17f6-400f-b97a-9510975d61e6", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "0b33cee732ea673dbcdbf5c31b550d474eebbe0cf6e8bed8096f7c6bae8aaad9", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "1\nThis info-sheet covers:\nAnnual General Meetings and Special \nGeneral Meetings  \nCOCo Legal Info-sheet\nPublished 07/10, Updated 07/12 and 05/18\n1  Why we hold general meetings \nOne reason that non-profits hold meetings with their membership is because the law says they are obligated \nto do so. This info-sheet was made to explain key legal requirements for these meetings.\nAs important as those legal responsibilities are, it\u2019s vital to avoid thinking about these meetings purely in \nterms of the law, or your meetings are sure to feel like a stressful chore. Meetings with our membership are  \na very important place to strengthen the democratic life of our organization, and strengthen the ability of our \ncommunity to work together for social change. They are a place where we can give our membership a real \nsay in major decisions that are being made about the structure, direction and governance of the organization.  \nCOCo believes that we should invest in ensuring that our meetings are spaces for community groups to \nfoster and sustain relationships, provide space for self-reflection and", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 1099, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "94cfbd58-17f6-400f-b97a-9510975d61e6": {"__data__": {"id_": "94cfbd58-17f6-400f-b97a-9510975d61e6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section covers the importance of Annual General Meetings and Special General Meetings for non-profit organizations. It emphasizes the legal obligations for holding these meetings but also highlights the significance of these gatherings in strengthening democratic processes within the organization and allowing members to have a say in important decisions. The section also mentions the role of meetings in fostering relationships and providing space for self-reflection within community groups.", "next_section_summary": "The key topics covered in this section include the importance of investing in meetings as spaces for community groups to foster relationships, self-reflection, and collective power. It also discusses strategies for creating effective meetings, finding applicable rules, scheduling Annual General Meetings (AGMs) and Special General Meetings (SGMs), choosing meeting locations, and setting the structure, direction, and governance of the organization. Key entities mentioned include the Comit\u00e9 sectoriel de main-d\u2019\u0153uvre (CSMO) and resources for further information on meeting strategies.", "section_summary": "The section emphasizes the importance of viewing meetings with members as opportunities to strengthen democratic processes within the organization and foster community relationships. It highlights the need to go beyond legal requirements and focus on creating spaces for self-reflection, critique, and collective power. The section also mentions resources from the Comit\u00e9 sectoriel de main-d\u2019\u0153uvre (CSMO) and an article on making AGMs more engaging and impactful.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How can non-profit organizations go beyond legal requirements to create meaningful and engaging Annual General Meetings and Special General Meetings that strengthen democratic processes and foster community relationships?\n2. What resources and strategies are available for organizations to make their meetings spaces for community groups to foster relationships, provide self-reflection and critique, and build collective power?\n3. How can organizations ensure that their meetings with members are not seen as a stressful chore, but rather as vital opportunities to involve members in major decisions regarding the structure, direction, and governance of the organization?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "c631f355-dd41-4a54-9a7e-7aa87c241786", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "55650bb8e4a595e342832c93108c642e108f4e2b23093ef72e456a7b9a843e77", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "07252161-1314-488a-8062-031ebdc040e1", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "bc07fab5db51e401f06c96e84602d3d7ce240bdeba6f4522aad6d716bfba184a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "652fc6b0-b8a0-4300-a9ba-b19a3cef3b43", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "3fa3fbb0b7f5d8f708a24d15d46c928110a7ed6a831c374aca2279c3d33babec", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "vital to avoid thinking about these meetings purely in \nterms of the law, or your meetings are sure to feel like a stressful chore. Meetings with our membership are  \na very important place to strengthen the democratic life of our organization, and strengthen the ability of our \ncommunity to work together for social change. They are a place where we can give our membership a real \nsay in major decisions that are being made about the structure, direction and governance of the organization.  \nCOCo believes that we should invest in ensuring that our meetings are spaces for community groups to \nfoster and sustain relationships, provide space for self-reflection and critique, and build collective power: in \nshort, to support the democratic life of social movements and community groups! \nFor more information on strategies about how to do this, see the resources listed at the end of this info-\nsheet, especially those produced by the Comit\u00e9 sectoriel de main-d\u2019\u0153uvre (CSMO), as well as our article \n\u201cHow to Make Your AGM Great, Not Just Necessary\u201d", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 430, "end_char_idx": 1483, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "652fc6b0-b8a0-4300-a9ba-b19a3cef3b43": {"__data__": {"id_": "652fc6b0-b8a0-4300-a9ba-b19a3cef3b43", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "1", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The section emphasizes the importance of viewing meetings with members as opportunities to strengthen democratic processes within the organization and foster community relationships. It highlights the need to go beyond legal requirements and focus on creating spaces for self-reflection, critique, and collective power. The section also mentions resources from the Comit\u00e9 sectoriel de main-d\u2019\u0153uvre (CSMO) and an article on making AGMs more engaging and impactful.", "next_section_summary": "The section provides information on the importance of holding general meetings, finding applicable rules, determining the timing for Annual General Meetings (AGM) and Special General Meetings (SGM), selecting a location for the meeting, setting the agenda, giving notice, establishing quorum, recording minutes, following meeting procedures, presenting financial statements, and conducting board elections. The content is likely sourced from the Comit\u00e9 sectoriel de main-d\u2019\u0153uvre (CSMO) and includes guidance on making AGMs effective and not just a necessary obligation.", "section_summary": "The key topics covered in this section include the importance of investing in meetings as spaces for community groups to foster relationsh