he issues the membership wants to address. \nAny member has the right to consult the list of names and addresses of the members of the organization, \nwhich can help them in preparing the request. When the directors receive such a request, they must call the \nSGM within 21 days. If they fail to do so, 10% of the membership may call an SGM themselves, even if they \nare not the same members who signed the initial request.\nThe by-laws can lower this percentage. If the Board is being", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1243, "end_char_idx": 2269, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "b4fc64c4-9bdb-4db4-bbd8-81148ce8c3d2": {"__data__": {"id_": "b4fc64c4-9bdb-4db4-bbd8-81148ce8c3d2", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "5", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the option for an organization to combine an SGM and an AGM for efficiency, the requirements for calling an SGM, the right of members to access a list of names and addresses of other members, and the consequences if the directors fail to call an SGM in response to a written request from members. The entities involved are the organization, its members, the executive committee, and the board of directors.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the requirements and procedures for federally incorporated non-profit organizations regarding special meetings of members (SGMs) and annual meetings of members. It explains that SGMs are where directors or the organization's public accountant can be removed by a simple majority, while all other decisions, including special resolutions, are made at annual meetings of members. Special resolutions require a 2/3 majority vote to pass. It also mentions that changes to bylaws for federally incorporated organizations can be made by the board and must be ratified by the membership at the next AGM or SGM.", "section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the process for calling a Special General Meeting (SGM) within an organization, the rights of members to request an SGM, and the potential actions members can take if the board is uncooperative in honoring the request. The entities involved are the organization's secretary, directors, members, and the Superior Court in the context of a mandamus request.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What is the process for calling a Special General Meeting (SGM) within an organization if the board of directors fails to do so in response to a written request from members?\n2. How can members of an organization ensure that their request for an SGM is honored if the board is uncooperative, and what legal recourse do they have in such a situation?\n3. What role does the organization's secretary play in the process of calling a Special General Meeting (SGM), and what rights do members have in accessing information to help prepare their request for an SGM?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "fdbf1e78-6297-4451-beae-74e92fd1de1f", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "5", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "425f1c561b3e9fd0a8967e5925403f156745b8af271ee60417870967d2a56e76", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "928a02ed-66d6-430d-9a67-ce381ab764cb", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "5", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "529ae50ed7676a4953de1365babaef6a92fa3df776ded86f694bf5660dd60424", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "organization\u2019s secretary receives a written \nrequest signed by 10% of the members, which sets out the issues the membership wants to address. \nAny member has the right to consult the list of names and addresses of the members of the organization, \nwhich can help them in preparing the request. When the directors receive such a request, they must call the \nSGM within 21 days. If they fail to do so, 10% of the membership may call an SGM themselves, even if they \nare not the same members who signed the initial request.\nThe by-laws can lower this percentage. If the Board is being uncooperative about honoring the request for \nan SGM, this can make it difficult for members to properly give notice of an SGM themselves, and to hold \none. An alternative is to make a mandamus request in Superior Court, asking the court to order the board to \nhold the meeting or risk being held in contempt.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1688, "end_char_idx": 2579, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "1d8de883-aee9-4bd1-bee8-b02ecf04c586": {"__data__": {"id_": "1d8de883-aee9-4bd1-bee8-b02ecf04c586", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the process for calling a Special General Meeting (SGM) within an organization, the rights of members to request an SGM, and the potential actions members can take if the board is uncooperative in honoring the request. The entities involved are the organization's secretary, directors, members, and the Superior Court in the context of a mandamus request.", "next_section_summary": "The key topics covered in this section include the definition of a \"special resolution\" under federal non-profit law, the process for changing by-laws for provincially and federally incorporated organizations, and the decision-making process for certain matters in federally incorporated organizations such as removing a director, electing directors, and appointing or removing the organization's public accountant. The entities involved in these processes are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the public accountant.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the requirements and procedures for federally incorporated non-profit organizations regarding special meetings of members (SGMs) and annual meetings of members. It explains that SGMs are where directors or the organization's public accountant can be removed by a simple majority, while all other decisions, including special resolutions, are made at annual meetings of members. Special resolutions require a 2/3 majority vote to pass. It also mentions that changes to bylaws for federally incorporated organizations can be made by the board and must be ratified by the membership at the next AGM or SGM.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What is the process for removing a director or the organization's public accountant in a federally incorporated non-profit organization?\n2. How are special resolutions defined and passed in federally incorporated non-profit organizations?\n3. What is the procedure for changing by-laws in both provincially and federally incorporated organizations, and how does it differ from other decision-making processes within the organization?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f4067c9d-8cf5-4f23-8054-0ab044d048c8", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "73f539d3293c14ed24cb02f0b8cdee59469dad58b5dfa35294dbf241d7712bca", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "677f8f01-4146-485d-b3f8-2fe85cf48cd6", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "c39cd2f02f094dc22c5e6fd779319113a0736985850e1e45e83f546b77de083c", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "6\nIf you are federally incorporated...\nFederal non-profit law calls SGMs \u201cspecial meetings of members\u201d. These meetings are the only place \nwhere directors, or the person serving as the organization\u2019s public accountant, can be removed, by simple \nmajority. All other decisions, including \"special resolutions\", are made at an \"annual meeting of members\". \nSpecial resolutions are those that require a special majority of votes to pass, that is, 2/3 of the vote.\n*The federal non-profit law defines a \u201cspecial resolution\u201d as one passed by a majority of not less than two \nthirds of the votes cast.  \n!\nBoth provincially and federally incorporated organizations don\u2019t have to call an \nSGM to change their by-laws. Instead, any changes to the bylaws take effect \nimmediately when the board adopts them. They must be ratified by the mem-\nbership at the next AGM to remain in force, or the next SGM, if one happens \nsooner.\nDecision (federally incorporated) Where? Votes Needed\n\u2022 Removing a director\n\u2022", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 995, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "677f8f01-4146-485d-b3f8-2fe85cf48cd6": {"__data__": {"id_": "677f8f01-4146-485d-b3f8-2fe85cf48cd6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section discusses the requirements and procedures for federally incorporated non-profit organizations regarding special meetings of members (SGMs) and annual meetings of members. It explains that SGMs are where directors or the organization's public accountant can be removed by a simple majority, while all other decisions, including special resolutions, are made at annual meetings of members. Special resolutions require a 2/3 majority vote to pass. It also mentions that changes to bylaws for federally incorporated organizations can be made by the board and must be ratified by the membership at the next AGM or SGM.", "next_section_summary": "This section outlines the decision-making processes and voting requirements for different actions at annual general meetings (AGM) and special general meetings (SGM) of federally incorporated organizations. Key topics include the removal of directors and public accountants, election of directors, appointment or removal of public accountants, by-law amendments, and approval of contracts. The entities involved in these decisions are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the public accountant.", "section_summary": "The key topics covered in this section include the definition of a \"special resolution\" under federal non-profit law, the process for changing by-laws for provincially and federally incorporated organizations, and the decision-making process for certain matters in federally incorporated organizations such as removing a director, electing directors, and appointing or removing the organization's public accountant. The entities involved in these processes are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the public accountant.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What is the definition of a \"special resolution\" under federal non-profit law?\n2. How can changes to bylaws for provincially and federally incorporated organizations be made and ratified?\n3. What are the specific decision-making processes and voting requirements for actions such as removing a director, electing directors, and appointing or removing the organization's public accountant in federally incorporated organizations?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f4067c9d-8cf5-4f23-8054-0ab044d048c8", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "73f539d3293c14ed24cb02f0b8cdee59469dad58b5dfa35294dbf241d7712bca", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "1d8de883-aee9-4bd1-bee8-b02ecf04c586", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "f078a19126ba9c5dc9a6895e99fb2e89cd7628e1310c7a48e11a7c043d9d0a55", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "9c1da810-9064-4653-befd-804cd6a25fad", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a035983e7036ce069d4cfac381d0ebc36569712a79cd354c8b9566ecd6150b78", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "federal non-profit law defines a \u201cspecial resolution\u201d as one passed by a majority of not less than two \nthirds of the votes cast.  \n!\nBoth provincially and federally incorporated organizations don\u2019t have to call an \nSGM to change their by-laws. Instead, any changes to the bylaws take effect \nimmediately when the board adopts them. They must be ratified by the mem-\nbership at the next AGM to remain in force, or the next SGM, if one happens \nsooner.\nDecision (federally incorporated) Where? Votes Needed\n\u2022 Removing a director\n\u2022 Removing the public accountant\nSGM only Ordinary resolu-\ntion\n\u2022 Electing directors\n\u2022 Fixing the number of directors to be elected at annual meetings \n(within the range set by the articles of incorporation)\n\u2022 Appointing or removing the organization\u2019s public accountant, or \nfixing their remuneration, or requiring that they carry out an audit\n\u2022 Confirming, rejecting, or amending changes or proposals to \nthe by-laws made by the board, except those that", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 466, "end_char_idx": 1448, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "9c1da810-9064-4653-befd-804cd6a25fad": {"__data__": {"id_": "9c1da810-9064-4653-befd-804cd6a25fad", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics covered in this section include the definition of a \"special resolution\" under federal non-profit law, the process for changing by-laws for provincially and federally incorporated organizations, and the decision-making process for certain matters in federally incorporated organizations such as removing a director, electing directors, and appointing or removing the organization's public accountant. The entities involved in these processes are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the public accountant.", "next_section_summary": "This section outlines the key responsibilities and decision-making processes that must be followed during an audit or general meeting (AGM) or special general meeting (SGM) of an organization. It covers topics such as confirming, rejecting, or amending changes to by-laws, amending by-laws to modify articles of incorporation, approving contracts with potential conflicts of interest, holding meetings outside of Canada, adopting resolutions in lieu of meetings, and resolving not to appoint a public accountant. The entities involved in these decisions include the board, members, and directors of the organization.", "section_summary": "This section outlines the decision-making processes and voting requirements for different actions at annual general meetings (AGM) and special general meetings (SGM) of federally incorporated organizations. Key topics include the removal of directors and public accountants, election of directors, appointment or removal of public accountants, by-law amendments, and approval of contracts. The entities involved in these decisions are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the public accountant.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the specific voting requirements for actions such as removing a director, electing directors, and appointing or removing the organization's public accountant at a special general meeting (SGM) of a federally incorporated organization?\n2. How are changes or proposals to the by-laws made by the board confirmed, rejected, or amended at an annual general meeting (AGM) or special general meeting (SGM) of a federally incorporated organization, and what is the voting threshold required for such decisions?\n3. In what circumstances can the by-laws be amended to modify the articles of incorporation, amalgamate with another entity, become a provincially regulated non-profit or other type of legal entity, dissolve, or liquidate the organization's assets at an AGM or SGM of a federally incorporated organization, and what is the voting requirement for such actions?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f4067c9d-8cf5-4f23-8054-0ab044d048c8", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "73f539d3293c14ed24cb02f0b8cdee59469dad58b5dfa35294dbf241d7712bca", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "677f8f01-4146-485d-b3f8-2fe85cf48cd6", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "2b78bf669f2ab4ea5574716eb7be0e7e91ff971a674c63cf52dcf42e99a16db8", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "de0d8147-eb0d-4914-8000-1bd0faebb104", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "27efe3a600fa09d05a31edd97d21a8ad200e020de9730d09d188d2adc8baeb82", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "SGM, if one happens \nsooner.\nDecision (federally incorporated) Where? Votes Needed\n\u2022 Removing a director\n\u2022 Removing the public accountant\nSGM only Ordinary resolu-\ntion\n\u2022 Electing directors\n\u2022 Fixing the number of directors to be elected at annual meetings \n(within the range set by the articles of incorporation)\n\u2022 Appointing or removing the organization\u2019s public accountant, or \nfixing their remuneration, or requiring that they carry out an audit\n\u2022 Confirming, rejecting, or amending changes or proposals to \nthe by-laws made by the board, except those that make \u201cfundamental \nchanges\u201d (see the following point)\nAGM or SGM \u200250% + 1\n(\u201cordinary resolu-\ntion\u201d)\n\u2022 Amending the by-laws to modify the articles of incorpora-\ntion, amalgamate with another entity, become a provincially regulated \nnon-profit or other type of legal entity, dissolve, or liquidate the organiza-\ntion\u2019s assets\n\u2022 Approving or ratifying a contract in which", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 889, "end_char_idx": 1817, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "de0d8147-eb0d-4914-8000-1bd0faebb104": {"__data__": {"id_": "de0d8147-eb0d-4914-8000-1bd0faebb104", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section outlines the decision-making processes and voting requirements for different actions at annual general meetings (AGM) and special general meetings (SGM) of federally incorporated organizations. Key topics include the removal of directors and public accountants, election of directors, appointment or removal of public accountants, by-law amendments, and approval of contracts. The entities involved in these decisions are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the public accountant.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the key topics related to decision-making processes within a regulated non-profit or other legal entity. It covers the approval or ratification of certain actions such as dissolving or liquidating the organization's assets, approving contracts with potential conflicts of interest, holding meetings outside of Canada, adopting resolutions without a meeting, and deciding not to appoint a public accountant. The section also outlines the majority required for each decision, with some requiring a 2/3 majority and others needing a unanimous decision from all members.", "section_summary": "This section outlines the key responsibilities and decision-making processes that must be followed during an audit or general meeting (AGM) or special general meeting (SGM) of an organization. It covers topics such as confirming, rejecting, or amending changes to by-laws, amending by-laws to modify articles of incorporation, approving contracts with potential conflicts of interest, holding meetings outside of Canada, adopting resolutions in lieu of meetings, and resolving not to appoint a public accountant. The entities involved in these decisions include the board, members, and directors of the organization.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the specific decision-making processes and voting requirements for actions such as amending by-laws to modify articles of incorporation, approving contracts with potential conflicts of interest, and holding meetings outside of Canada within a regulated non-profit or other legal entity?\n2. How does the approval process differ for decisions requiring a 50% + 1 majority, a 2/3 majority, and a unanimous decision from all members at an annual general meeting (AGM) or special general meeting (SGM) of an organization?\n3. What are the key responsibilities and decision-making processes that must be followed during an audit or general meeting (AGM) or special general meeting (SGM) of an organization, particularly in relation to confirming, rejecting, or amending changes to by-laws, amending by-laws to modify articles of incorporation, and resolving not to appoint a public accountant?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f4067c9d-8cf5-4f23-8054-0ab044d048c8", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "73f539d3293c14ed24cb02f0b8cdee59469dad58b5dfa35294dbf241d7712bca", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "9c1da810-9064-4653-befd-804cd6a25fad", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "f07966923728d20e04fbc697df2a74d7b57b813a1f2741bbec8de594ecf542a0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "9a2525f1-5c26-4ae1-9da9-2f3bf96ecc0d", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "fead4915fd5bd8b1bacd248d0d8989892a30038622b97738589f84d5884368ec", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "carry out an audit\n\u2022 Confirming, rejecting, or amending changes or proposals to \nthe by-laws made by the board, except those that make \u201cfundamental \nchanges\u201d (see the following point)\nAGM or SGM \u200250% + 1\n(\u201cordinary resolu-\ntion\u201d)\n\u2022 Amending the by-laws to modify the articles of incorpora-\ntion, amalgamate with another entity, become a provincially regulated \nnon-profit or other type of legal entity, dissolve, or liquidate the organiza-\ntion\u2019s assets\n\u2022 Approving or ratifying a contract in which a director has a poten-\ntial conflict-of-interest\nAGM or SGM 2/3 majority \n(\u201cspecial resolu-\ntion\u201d)\n\u2022 Holding a general meeting outside of Canada (this approval is \nnot necessary if the articles of incorporation explicitly allow it)\n\u2022 Adopting a resolution in lieu of a meeting (must be signed by all \nmembers)\n\u2022 Resolving not to appoint a public accountant\nAGM or SGM Unaminous", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1319, "end_char_idx": 2196, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "9a2525f1-5c26-4ae1-9da9-2f3bf96ecc0d": {"__data__": {"id_": "9a2525f1-5c26-4ae1-9da9-2f3bf96ecc0d", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section outlines the key responsibilities and decision-making processes that must be followed during an audit or general meeting (AGM) or special general meeting (SGM) of an organization. It covers topics such as confirming, rejecting, or amending changes to by-laws, amending by-laws to modify articles of incorporation, approving contracts with potential conflicts of interest, holding meetings outside of Canada, adopting resolutions in lieu of meetings, and resolving not to appoint a public accountant. The entities involved in these decisions include the board, members, and directors of the organization.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the voting process for organizations with different classes of members, advising consultation of additional resources for more complex situations. It also addresses the location requirements for holding an Annual General Meeting (AGM), stating that federally incorporated organizations must hold their AGM in Canada, while provincially incorporated organizations must hold it in Quebec unless otherwise specified in their constitution or by-laws. The section suggests obtaining email confirmation from all members agreeing to hold the meeting elsewhere if necessary.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the key topics related to decision-making processes within a regulated non-profit or other legal entity. It covers the approval or ratification of certain actions such as dissolving or liquidating the organization's assets, approving contracts with potential conflicts of interest, holding meetings outside of Canada, adopting resolutions without a meeting, and deciding not to appoint a public accountant. The section also outlines the majority required for each decision, with some requiring a 2/3 majority and others needing a unanimous decision from all members.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the key decision-making processes that must be followed during an audit or general meeting (AGM) or special general meeting (SGM) of an organization, including topics such as amending by-laws, approving contracts with conflicts of interest, and holding meetings outside of Canada?\n2. What are the voting process requirements for organizations with different classes of members, and what are the location requirements for holding an Annual General Meeting (AGM) for federally and provincially incorporated organizations?\n3. What are the specific actions that require a 2/3 majority or a unanimous decision from all members during an AGM or SGM, such as dissolving or liquidating the organization's assets, approving contracts with conflicts of interest, and resolving not to appoint a public accountant?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f4067c9d-8cf5-4f23-8054-0ab044d048c8", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "73f539d3293c14ed24cb02f0b8cdee59469dad58b5dfa35294dbf241d7712bca", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "de0d8147-eb0d-4914-8000-1bd0faebb104", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "6", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "53264d14b87caa5bfa01b96a9731a84b73406c7a00ef14e68a5b1188d8ef96ad", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "regulated \nnon-profit or other type of legal entity, dissolve, or liquidate the organiza-\ntion\u2019s assets\n\u2022 Approving or ratifying a contract in which a director has a poten-\ntial conflict-of-interest\nAGM or SGM 2/3 majority \n(\u201cspecial resolu-\ntion\u201d)\n\u2022 Holding a general meeting outside of Canada (this approval is \nnot necessary if the articles of incorporation explicitly allow it)\n\u2022 Adopting a resolution in lieu of a meeting (must be signed by all \nmembers)\n\u2022 Resolving not to appoint a public accountant\nAGM or SGM Unaminous deci-\nsion*", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1669, "end_char_idx": 2208, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "70107bbf-cfee-47f3-a8c7-843b91ea6291": {"__data__": {"id_": "70107bbf-cfee-47f3-a8c7-843b91ea6291", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section discusses the key topics related to decision-making processes within a regulated non-profit or other legal entity. It covers the approval or ratification of certain actions such as dissolving or liquidating the organization's assets, approving contracts with potential conflicts of interest, holding meetings outside of Canada, adopting resolutions without a meeting, and deciding not to appoint a public accountant. The section also outlines the majority required for each decision, with some requiring a 2/3 majority and others needing a unanimous decision from all members.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses where to hold your annual general meeting (AGM) based on whether your organization is federally or provincially incorporated, as well as the requirements for setting the agenda for the meeting. It also mentions that directors typically set the agenda for general meetings, and special general meetings (SGMs) will address specific issues for which they were called.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the voting process for organizations with different classes of members, advising consultation of additional resources for more complex situations. It also addresses the location requirements for holding an Annual General Meeting (AGM), stating that federally incorporated organizations must hold their AGM in Canada, while provincially incorporated organizations must hold it in Quebec unless otherwise specified in their constitution or by-laws. The section suggests obtaining email confirmation from all members agreeing to hold the meeting elsewhere if necessary.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the specific requirements for holding an Annual General Meeting (AGM) for federally incorporated organizations in Canada?\n2. How can organizations with different classes of members navigate the voting process during meetings?\n3. What resources are recommended for organizations facing more complex decision-making processes, such as dissolving assets or approving contracts with conflicts of interest?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "da58d603-ea36-41f1-858e-85ee40de5b74", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "2a13e90b035bebc528e19b78e894d7d60c18359a4c8ba74211ebc98abbf4bd3f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "e2393b83-f7d2-4a44-add5-686d92876d6b", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a0bb8b39cddc8907c733b9273591b6f4ec144a59f53e83aecb79256ec97d46f0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "7\n* In special situations, such as if the organization has different classes of members, the voting process may be \nmore complicated than what is listed above, and you should consult other resources, such as the more comprehen-\nsive table from which the one above was adapted, provided in La corporation sans but lucratif au Qu\u00e9bec : aspects \nth\u00e9oriques et pratiques by Paul Martel (Montr\u00e9al: Wilson & Lafleur, looseleaf version updated to January 2017), \nvolume 1 at pages 14-75 to 14-79, as well as 8-18 and following.\n5  Where to hold your meeting\nIf you are federally incorporated, by default, you must hold your AGM in Canada. If you are provincially incor-\nporated you must hold your AGM in Quebec. You can meet elsewhere if your constitution explicitly allows it, \nor if every member with the right to vote at the meeting agrees to it beforehand. An email confirmation from \neach member agreeing to hold the meeting elsewhere could be sufficient.\nYour constitution or by-laws are also", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 991, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "e2393b83-f7d2-4a44-add5-686d92876d6b": {"__data__": {"id_": "e2393b83-f7d2-4a44-add5-686d92876d6b", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section discusses the voting process for organizations with different classes of members, advising consultation of additional resources for more complex situations. It also addresses the location requirements for holding an Annual General Meeting (AGM), stating that federally incorporated organizations must hold their AGM in Canada, while provincially incorporated organizations must hold it in Quebec unless otherwise specified in their constitution or by-laws. The section suggests obtaining email confirmation from all members agreeing to hold the meeting elsewhere if necessary.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the process of setting the agenda for an Annual General Meeting (AGM) and Special General Meeting (SGM). It explains that directors typically set the agenda for a general meeting, with an SGM's agenda focusing on the issues it was called to address. The section also outlines standard topics that are commonly included on an AGM agenda, such as approving minutes from previous meetings and presenting activities from the past year. It emphasizes the importance of following any restrictions set out in the organization's constitution or by-laws regarding where meetings can be held.", "section_summary": "This section discusses where to hold your annual general meeting (AGM) based on whether your organization is federally or provincially incorporated, as well as the requirements for setting the agenda for the meeting. It also mentions that directors typically set the agenda for general meetings, and special general meetings (SGMs) will address specific issues for which they were called.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the default location requirements for holding an Annual General Meeting (AGM) for federally and provincially incorporated organizations in Canada?\n2. How can an organization hold their AGM in a location other than the default requirement, according to the information provided in this context?\n3. Who typically sets the agenda for a general meeting, and what specific topics are commonly included on an AGM agenda, as outlined in the document?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "da58d603-ea36-41f1-858e-85ee40de5b74", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "2a13e90b035bebc528e19b78e894d7d60c18359a4c8ba74211ebc98abbf4bd3f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "70107bbf-cfee-47f3-a8c7-843b91ea6291", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "ff23dbe576010cbbc3b3db27ee4d802eaddbad8ba7f3bca08a6583dafeeb3a48", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "008e03a3-f879-499d-a005-919f4660b853", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "7c4d55cf76956ef042745aa0ccc9ac81d3b2e68ab02e8a4462b71326352b200a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "2017), \nvolume 1 at pages 14-75 to 14-79, as well as 8-18 and following.\n5  Where to hold your meeting\nIf you are federally incorporated, by default, you must hold your AGM in Canada. If you are provincially incor-\nporated you must hold your AGM in Quebec. You can meet elsewhere if your constitution explicitly allows it, \nor if every member with the right to vote at the meeting agrees to it beforehand. An email confirmation from \neach member agreeing to hold the meeting elsewhere could be sufficient.\nYour constitution or by-laws are also able to further restrict where you can hold general \nmeetings to say that, for example, they must be held in Montreal.\n6 Setting the agenda...  \nDirectors are generally the ones who set the agenda of topics to be discussed at a general meeting. An \nSGM\u2019s agenda will include the issues it was called to address. For example, if the SGM was called as a \nresult of a valid request from members to do so, the topics they indicated must", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 448, "end_char_idx": 1424, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "008e03a3-f879-499d-a005-919f4660b853": {"__data__": {"id_": "008e03a3-f879-499d-a005-919f4660b853", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section discusses where to hold your annual general meeting (AGM) based on whether your organization is federally or provincially incorporated, as well as the requirements for setting the agenda for the meeting. It also mentions that directors typically set the agenda for general meetings, and special general meetings (SGMs) will address specific issues for which they were called.", "next_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the approval of minutes from previous AGMs, presentation of activities over the past year, presentation of annual financial statements, and presentation of the accountant's report. The entities involved in these topics are the board, members, and decision-makers of the organization.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the process of setting the agenda for an Annual General Meeting (AGM) and Special General Meeting (SGM). It explains that directors typically set the agenda for a general meeting, with an SGM's agenda focusing on the issues it was called to address. The section also outlines standard topics that are commonly included on an AGM agenda, such as approving minutes from previous meetings and presenting activities from the past year. It emphasizes the importance of following any restrictions set out in the organization's constitution or by-laws regarding where meetings can be held.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the standard topics that are commonly included on the agenda for an Annual General Meeting (AGM)?\n2. Who typically sets the agenda for a general meeting, and what topics are included on a Special General Meeting (SGM) agenda?\n3. How can the location for holding a general meeting be determined, and what restrictions may be set out in an organization's constitution or by-laws regarding meeting locations?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "da58d603-ea36-41f1-858e-85ee40de5b74", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "2a13e90b035bebc528e19b78e894d7d60c18359a4c8ba74211ebc98abbf4bd3f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "e2393b83-f7d2-4a44-add5-686d92876d6b", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "20