e", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "da58d603-ea36-41f1-858e-85ee40de5b74", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "2a13e90b035bebc528e19b78e894d7d60c18359a4c8ba74211ebc98abbf4bd3f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "008e03a3-f879-499d-a005-919f4660b853", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "8b56e0c8b813518448a73d4e669adca377b7df5ed492b9f93bab72ee45293fe8", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "560db0e8-332c-4163-a299-a0b14280c3cb", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "d3e6a5fdcf80bae4cbb52221846a25ed0a2e72affeff801ad154c4d5f505b0c3", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "to address. For example, if the SGM was called as a \nresult of a valid request from members to do so, the topics they indicated must appear on the agenda. The \nboard can, however, also add further topics at its discretion.\nWhat topics should be on the agenda for discussion at an AGM? A number of topics are standard, though \nmost of these are not strictly necessary:\nPresent and approve minutes of previous years' AGM: \n\u2022 it is common for organizations vote to approve the minutes taken at the previous year\u2019s AGM;\nPresentation of activities over the past year:\n\u2022 it is common for organizations to present their activities over the past year to the membership,  \n including reports from the Board and other decision-makers;\nPresentation of annual financial statements:\n\u2022 the Board is required to present the organizations\u2019 annual financial statements and any other finan \n cial information required by your constitution or by-laws (for details, see Section 11 \u2013 Presenting  \n financial statements), and must allow the membership to ask questions about them;\nPresentation of accountant's report\n\u2022 if your organization", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1292, "end_char_idx": 2409, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "560db0e8-332c-4163-a299-a0b14280c3cb": {"__data__": {"id_": "560db0e8-332c-4163-a299-a0b14280c3cb", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the approval of minutes from previous AGMs, presentation of activities over the past year, presentation of annual financial statements, and presentation of the accountant's report. The entities involved in these topics are the board, members, and decision-makers of the organization.", "next_section_summary": "The section discusses the requirements for appointing an auditor or public accountant, voting on by-law/constitutional changes, electing new directors, voting on resolutions/contracts, addressing funders concerns or questions, and discussing any other business under the category of \"Varia.\" It also mentions the possibility of holding elections by mail or at a special general meeting for provincially incorporated non-profits.", "section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the approval of minutes from the previous year's AGM, presentation of activities over the past year, presentation of annual financial statements, presentation of accountant's report, and approval of financial statements. The entities involved in this section are the organization's Board, decision-makers, auditor or public accountant, and the membership.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the key topics typically covered during an organization's Annual General Meeting (AGM), including the approval of minutes, presentation of activities, financial statements, and accountant's report?\n2. What entities are typically involved in the presentation and approval of financial information at an AGM, including the organization's Board, decision-makers, auditor or public accountant, and membership?\n3. What are the common procedures for presenting and approving financial statements at an AGM, including allowing the membership to ask questions, voting on approval, and presenting reports from auditors or accountants?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "da58d603-ea36-41f1-858e-85ee40de5b74", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "2a13e90b035bebc528e19b78e894d7d60c18359a4c8ba74211ebc98abbf4bd3f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "a95c6c7d-09a5-417e-9997-d110063c70ee", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "7", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "e4e43097cba60d57870534cf32d46a0c735e4dfa5e0e5a696acace53c8edaa11", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "common for organizations vote to approve the minutes taken at the previous year\u2019s AGM;\nPresentation of activities over the past year:\n\u2022 it is common for organizations to present their activities over the past year to the membership,  \n including reports from the Board and other decision-makers;\nPresentation of annual financial statements:\n\u2022 the Board is required to present the organizations\u2019 annual financial statements and any other finan \n cial information required by your constitution or by-laws (for details, see Section 11 \u2013 Presenting  \n financial statements), and must allow the membership to ask questions about them;\nPresentation of accountant's report\n\u2022 if your organization has named an auditor or public accountant, their report on your financial state \n ments must also be presented;\nApproval of financial statements\n\u2022 it is common for organizations to hold a vote to approve the financial statements and any report  \n given by the auditor or public accountant;", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1721, "end_char_idx": 2699, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "732116b3-3008-46c2-ba14-44b7669ad01e": {"__data__": {"id_": "732116b3-3008-46c2-ba14-44b7669ad01e", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "8", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the approval of minutes from the previous year's AGM, presentation of activities over the past year, presentation of annual financial statements, presentation of accountant's report, and approval of financial statements. The entities involved in this section are the organization's Board, decision-makers, auditor or public accountant, and the membership.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the key topics and entities involved in an annual general meeting (AGM) for organizations. It covers the election of directors, voting on resolutions/contracts, addressing funders' concerns or questions, and discussing any other business (AOB) under a \"varia\" agenda. Provincially incorporated non-profits may have the ability to authorize the chair to reorder agenda items. It is also recommended to allow discussion on topics indicated by members.", "section_summary": "The section discusses the requirements for appointing an auditor or public accountant, voting on by-law/constitutional changes, electing new directors, voting on resolutions/contracts, addressing funders concerns or questions, and discussing any other business under the category of \"Varia.\" It also mentions the possibility of holding elections by mail or at a special general meeting for provincially incorporated non-profits.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How can organizations address funders' concerns or questions during an annual general meeting (AGM)?\n2. What are the requirements for appointing an auditor or public accountant at an AGM for provincially incorporated non-profits or federally incorporated organizations?\n3. In what circumstances may elections for new directors be unnecessary at an AGM, according to the organization's by-laws or regulations for provincially incorporated non-profits?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_d