_section_summary": "This section discusses the various methods by which organizations can provide notice of meetings to their members, including electronic means, notice boards, publications, and newspapers. It also outlines the requirements for what must be included in the notice, as well as the option for organizations to request special permission from Corporations Canada for alternative notification methods.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the requirements for giving notice to members of federally incorporated organizations. It outlines the different methods of giving notice, such as by mail, courier, personal delivery, electronic communication, or publication in an organization's publication. The bylaws of the organization determine how notice must be given, and certain methods may be required based on the number of members in the organization.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the specific methods for giving notice to members of federally incorporated organizations, as outlined in the bylaws?\n2. How does the size of an organization impact the options available for providing notice of meetings to members?\n3. In what circumstances can federally incorporated organizations use electronic means to give notice to their members, and what alternative methods must be provided in conjunction with electronic communication?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f1da6ce9-7715-4589-af33-1241161c8917", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "10", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16