ecord date, and what are the default rules in such a scenario?\n3. How does the concept of a \"record date\" in relation to general meetings of a company affect membership participation, communication, and the overall turnout for general meetings?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "f1da6ce9-7715-4589-af33-1241161c8917", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "10", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "395f1bd50ebe3e5c62bafaed33b0b417cf778d8bad2d1ba1f76c74abf284a922", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "3c97f72f-6421-4d9b-82f1-56fe4b55d327", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "10", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "d3be6e904e6963127d852dc4bfc17980ab704ece1c26677c79e78da28e161455", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "been a \nmember at the time of the \u201crecord date\u201d. The directors can fix this date at anywhere between \n60 and 21 days before the general meeting takes place. The law strangely lets them set one \ndate at which time a person has to be a member to be entitled to receive notice of the meeting, \nand set a different date at which time a person has to be a member to be entitled to vote at the \nmeeting. If the directors don\u2019t set a record date for notice, then it\u2019s set at the end of the business \nday before notice was given (or the day of the meeting, if no notice was given). If no record date \nis fixed for the right to vote, then it\u2019s the same as the record date for the right to receive notice.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 2327, "end_char_idx": 3022, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "4e8b1b8e-b65e-4b35-9954-f6b3446ba6c6": {"__data__": {"id_": "4e8b1b8e-b65e-4b35-9954-f6b3446ba6c6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the concept of a \"record date\" in relation to general meetings of a company, the authority of directors to set this date between 60 and 21 days before the meeting, and the implications for members in terms of receiving notice and voting rights based on their membership status on the record date. The section also highlights the legal requirements and options for setting a record date for notice and voting rights, as well as the default rules if the directors do not specify a record date. Key entities mentioned in this section are the directors of the company and the members who are affected by the record date decisions.", "next_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the importance of quorum in general meetings of non-profit organizations, ways to encourage membership participation, and the different ways quorum can be defined in the by-laws. The section also mentions that if quorum is not specified in the by-laws, it automatically becomes the majority of members with the right to vote. Additionally, it states that quorum for provincially incorporated non-profits can't be less than two people according to the law.", "section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the definition of quorum, its importance in ensuring the validity of a general meeting, and the potential frustration it may cause. It also discusses the purpose of quorum in preventing a small group of members from making decisions on behalf of the entire membership. Additionally, the section mentions that if quorum is not specified in the by-laws, it automatically becomes the majority of members with the right to vote. The section also touches on ways to encourage membership participation to ensure a healthy turnout for general meetings and foster communication.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How is quorum defined in the context of general meetings of non-profit organizations, and what is its significance in ensuring the validity of such meetings?\n2. What are the implications of not meeting the quorum requirement for a general meeting, and how does it impact the decision-making process within the organization?\n3. How can organizations encourage membership participation to ensure a healthy turnout for general meetings and foster effective communication among members?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "1fd989f1-70ba-439a-a58d-93c39d17138c", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "7e3416074cb227e7a0803bb606f15f631de26838658e13bf732c64824da5e162", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "edadb228-5f50-4d63-919d-726c9fc830e6", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "a04bf1ffbdec169fa49dcfece89d82cf3763475eea73044b2f7b4a01cc10b8c1", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "11\n8  Quorum\nQuorum is the minimum number of people who have to attend a meeting. Without quorum, the entire gen-\neral meeting is invalid, although members are free to meet, without their decisions having any effect other \nthan as recommendations.\nFrustration with quorum is common. But it also serves an important purpose by preventing a small pro-\nportion of the membership from being burdened with having to decide whether they can legitimately make \nimportant structural decisions, and by preventing them from making decisions that the other members \noppose. Efforts to encourage membership participation can be a good (and often fun) way of ensuring a \nhealthy turn out for general meetings. It also helps with fostering healthy lines of communication. \nhttp://www.stickpng.com/assets/images/585e4ae1cb11b227491c3393.png \nIf quorum is not specified in the by-laws, then it automatically becomes the majority of the \nmembers with the right to vote.\nWhat can a quorum look like?\nQuorum can be set as a fixed number of members, a", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 0, "end_char_idx": 1031, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "edadb228-5f50-4d63-919d-726c9fc830e6": {"__data__": {"id_": "edadb228-5f50-4d63-919d-726c9fc830e6", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the definition of quorum, its importance in ensuring the validity of a general meeting, and the potential frustration it may cause. It also discusses the purpose of quorum in preventing a small group of members from making decisions on behalf of the entire membership. Additionally, the section mentions that if quorum is not specified in the by-laws, it automatically becomes the majority of members with the right to vote. The section also touches on ways to encourage membership participation to ensure a healthy turnout for general meetings and foster communication.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the concept of quorum in non-profit organizations, including how it can be determined (fixed number, percentage, formula), the minimum quorum requirements for provincially and federally incorporated non-profits, and whether quorum needs to be maintained throughout a meeting according to the by-laws. Key entities mentioned include members with the right to vote and the by-laws of the organization.", "section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the importance of quorum in general meetings of non-profit organizations, ways to encourage membership participation, and the different ways quorum can be defined in the by-laws. The section also mentions that if quorum is not specified in the by-laws, it automatically becomes the majority of members with the right to vote. Additionally, it states that quorum for provincially incorporated non-profits can't be less than two people according to the law.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How can quorum be defined in the by-laws of a non-profit organization?\n2. What is the minimum quorum requirement for provincially incorporated non-profits according to the law?\n3. What are some ways to encourage membership participation in general meetings of non-profit organizations to ensure a healthy turnout and foster communication?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "fi