nt that is determined or determinable by a formula. At the minimal ex-\ntreme, the by-laws can state that \u201cthe members who are present form a quorum\u201d.\nMany non-profits set a lower threshold for quorum in their by-laws. \nWhat's the lowest quorum that a non-profit can have?\nQuorum for provincially incorporated non-profits can\u2019t be less than two people: \nthe law says", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 486, "end_char_idx": 1435, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "0ea387d1-2fb2-4fa4-99c5-507b9f99b639": {"__data__": {"id_": "0ea387d1-2fb2-4fa4-99c5-507b9f99b639", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include the importance of quorum in general meetings of non-profit organizations, ways to encourage membership participation, and the different ways quorum can be defined in the by-laws. The section also mentions that if quorum is not specified in the by-laws, it automatically becomes the majority of members with the right to vote. Additionally, it states that quorum for provincially incorporated non-profits can't be less than two people according to the law.", "next_section_summary": "The section discusses the concept of quorum for non-profit organizations, stating that provincially incorporated non-profits must have a minimum quorum of two people, while federally incorporated non-profits can have a meeting with just one person. It also addresses whether quorum needs to be maintained throughout a meeting, with by-laws determining the requirements. Additionally, it mentions that notice is not required to resume a meeting adjourned for a specified time of 30 days or less.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the concept of quorum in non-profit organizations, including how it can be determined (fixed number, percentage, formula), the minimum quorum requirements for provincially and federally incorporated non-profits, and whether quorum needs to be maintained throughout a meeting according to the by-laws. Key entities mentioned include members with the right to vote and the by-laws of the organization.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the different ways in which quorum can be defined in the by-laws of a non-profit organization?\n2. What is the minimum quorum requirement for provincially incorporated non-profits according to the law?\n3. Can a general meeting of a federally incorporated non-profit be validly held by just one person?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "1fd989f1-70ba-439a-a58d-93c39d17138c", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "7e3416074cb227e7a0803bb606f15f631de26838658e13bf732c64824da5e162", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "edadb228-5f50-4d63-919d-726c9fc830e6", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "d0dfdbad2eb9a3794a9257af5b7e4007de17d65b4196225a167b3fe69877732b", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "58eb867e-5f86-43b4-926e-d6483b3d51ca", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "bd250df1a177190bc3d5b286c6bf923e0385ebcdf9ba46348fd2b832ee4e144f", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "the \nmembers with the right to vote.\nWhat can a quorum look like?\nQuorum can be set as a fixed number of members, a percentage of their total, or \nan amount that is determined or determinable by a formula. At the minimal ex-\ntreme, the by-laws can state that \u201cthe members who are present form a quorum\u201d.\nMany non-profits set a lower threshold for quorum in their by-laws. \nWhat's the lowest quorum that a non-profit can have?\nQuorum for provincially incorporated non-profits can\u2019t be less than two people: \nthe law says that one member can\u2019t \u201cmeet\u201d with themself. If your organization has \nonly one member, your by-laws can set the quorum to be one member who is \nrepresented at the meeting by at least two people. One person on their own can, \nhowever, validly hold a general meeting of a federally incorporated non-profit.\nDoes quorum need to be maintained throughout a meeting?\nThe by-laws can set whether quorum must be maintained throughout the meeting", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 916, "end_char_idx": 1873, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "58eb867e-5f86-43b4-926e-d6483b3d51ca": {"__data__": {"id_": "58eb867e-5f86-43b4-926e-d6483b3d51ca", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section discusses the concept of quorum in non-profit organizations, including how it can be determined (fixed number, percentage, formula), the minimum quorum requirements for provincially and federally incorporated non-profits, and whether quorum needs to be maintained throughout a meeting according to the by-laws. Key entities mentioned include members with the right to vote and the by-laws of the organization.", "next_section_summary": "The section discusses the importance of meeting minutes as a written summary of key points and decisions made during a meeting. It emphasizes the need to record who gave presentations, the substance of decisions, and the names of directors elected. It also mentions the importance of recording for and against each decision, as well as the number of abstentions. The section highlights the storage of minutes with other corporate records at the head office and the recording of signed resolutions made in lieu of a general meeting.", "section_summary": "The section discusses the concept of quorum for non-profit organizations, stating that provincially incorporated non-profits must have a minimum quorum of two people, while federally incorporated non-profits can have a meeting with just one person. It also addresses whether quorum needs to be maintained throughout a meeting, with by-laws determining the requirements. Additionally, it mentions that notice is not required to resume a meeting adjourned for a specified time of 30 days or less.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What is the minimum quorum requirement for provincially incorporated non-profits according to the law?\n2. Can a general meeting of a federally incorporated non-profit be validly held by just one person?\n3. Do by-laws determine whether quorum must be maintained throughout a meeting for provincially incorporated non-profits?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "1fd989f1-70ba-439a-a58d-93c39d17138c", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "7e3416074cb227e7a0803bb606f15f631de26838658e13bf732c64824da5e162", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "0ea387d1-2fb2-4fa4-99c5-507b9f99b639", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "11", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "46cce396bab6bd40720f9b9e435ceeb362d36e5b5b0453d9aeabd5e4ef390af4", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "the lowest quorum that a non-profit can have?\nQuorum for provincially incorporated non-profits can\u2019t be less than two people: \nthe law says that one member can\u2019t \u201cmeet\u201d with themself. If your organization has \nonly one member, your by-laws can set the quorum to be one member who is \nrepresented at the meeting by at least two people. One person on their own can, \nhowever, validly hold a general meeting of a federally incorporated non-profit.\nDoes quorum need to be maintained throughout a meeting?\nThe by-laws can set whether quorum must be maintained throughout the meeting \nor is only needed to open the meeting. If they say nothing about this issue, then \nquorum must be maintained for the whole meeting for provincially incorporated \nnon-profits, while federally incorporated non-profits only need quorum to open it.\nNotice does not need to be given to resume a meeting that was adjourned for a specified time of 30 days or less.\n?\n!", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1296, "end_char_idx": 2236, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "6b8017e9-f9f9-4145-9dde-9171d71b9408": {"__data__": {"id_": "6b8017e9-f9f9-4145-9dde-9171d71b9408", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "12", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The section discusses the concept of quorum for non-profit organizations, stating that provincially incorporated non-profits must have a minimum quorum of two people, while federally incorporated non-profits can have a meeting with just one person. It also addresses whether quorum needs to be maintained throughout a meeting, with by-laws determining the requirements. Additionally, it mentions that notice is not required to resume a meeting adjourned for a specified time of 30 days or less.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the importance of recording and storing minutes of general meetings for organizations. It highlights the need to document voting results, resolutions, and declarations made by the meeting chair. The section also emphasizes the requirement to store minutes with other corporate records at the head office, or as designated for federally incorporated non-profits. It specifies the signing of minutes by designated individuals for provincially incorporated non-profits and outlines member access to meeting minutes and reports. Additionally, it mentions that the board of such organizations decides on granting access to meeting minutes upon request.", "section_summary": "The section discusses t