inutes by designated individuals for provincially incorporated non-profits and outlines member access to meeting minutes and reports. Additionally, it mentions that the board of such organizations decides on granting access to meeting minutes upon request.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses general meetings and meeting procedures for organizations. It mentions that members have the right to access meeting minutes and reports, and that the board decides on granting access. It also explains the role of a chairperson in presiding over a general meeting, and the factors to consider when choosing a chair. Additionally, it highlights the importance of ensuring valid notice of the meeting for provincially incorporated organizations.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the importance of keeping accurate records of general meetings for both federally and provincially incorporated non-profit organizations. It highlights the need to store signed resolutions and minutes of general meetings in a secure manner. It also mentions the importance of members being able to access these records and the role of the board in granting such access. Additionally, it touches on meeting procedures, including the role of a chairperson and the importance of considering potential divisive issues when selecting a chair.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How should minutes of general meetings be stored for provincially incorporated non-profits, and who is responsible for signing them?\n2. What role does the board play in granting access to meeting minutes and reports for members of provincially incorporated non-profit organizations?\n3. What factors should be considered when selecting a chairperson to preside over a general meeting, especially in relation to potentially divisive issues?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "