ements.\n!\nIt is an offence for a federally incorporated non-profit to publish or dissemi -\nnate these financial statements if they are not approved and signed, or if they \nare not accompanied by the public accountant\u2019s report, if one was produced. \nCertain particularities apply to the presentation of financial information by feder-\nally incorporated organizations at their AGMs. For example: Federally incorporat-\ned non-profits must send their members a copy or a summary of all the financial \ndocuments they are required to present at the annual meeting. If a summary is \nprovided, the non-profit must indicate how members can obtain a full copy at no \ncost. To lessen this burdensome obligation, your organization can instead provide \nin its by-laws to notify its", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 971, "end_char_idx": 2109, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "2ef4a3c4-0f38-4749-a39e-a98d4eb1f4e9": {"__data__": {"id_": "2ef4a3c4-0f38-4749-a39e-a98d4eb1f4e9", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "16", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The section discusses the obligations and requirements for federally incorporated non-profit organizations related to financial statements at their Annual General Meetings (AGMs). Key topics include the signing of financial statements by directors, the attachment and presentation of a public accountant's report, and the dissemination of financial information to members. It is emphasized that it is an offence to publish or disseminate financial statements that are not approved and signed, or not accompanied by the public accountant's report. Additionally, there are specific obligations for federally incorporated non-profits with subsidiaries. The section also mentions the option of providing a summary of financial documents to members, with instructions on how to obtain a full copy at no cost.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the level of scrutiny required for federally incorporated non-profits based on their gross annual income and whether they are considered a \"soliciting corporation\". It outlines the requirements for different categories of non-profits in terms of naming a public accountant and the intensity of review by the accountant. The section also mentions the definition of \"public sources\" and directs readers to Corporations Canada's website for more information. Key entities mentioned include federally incorporated non-profits, public accountants, and Corporations Canada.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the requirements for presenting financial information at annual general meetings (AGMs) for federally incorporated organizations. It mentions that financial statements must be approved and signed, and if applicable, accompanied by a public accountant's report. It also outlines specific requirements for federally incorporated non-profits, such as sending members copies or summaries of financial documents and providing access to full copies at no cost. Additionally, it suggests ways to streamline this process, such as notifying members that documents are available at the organization's head office for free.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the specific requirements for federally incorporated non-profit organizations in terms of presenting financial information at their Annual General Meetings (AGMs)?\n2. How can federally incorporated non-profits streamline the process of providing financial documents to their members, as suggested in the document?\n3. What are the consequences for federally incorporated non-profits if they fail to have their financial statements approved and signed, or if they are not accompanied by a public accountant's report at their AGMs?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "3b056607-e0c2-4906-8634-a50be5a38bc0", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "16", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "48fc08e90168d1ab4fcef74ba397cfb15c02551bfa04b419e9983f40863bd109", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "4ec2240c-2233-4d62-80f4-c70fc23787b2", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "16", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "f421f5f6105d408773f1a4720809bf6ee064b3032ac8d774caac8fb0415550e7", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "not approved and signed, or if they \nare not accompanied by the public accountant\u2019s report, if one was produced. \nCertain particularities apply to the presentation of financial information by feder-\nally incorporated organizations at their AGMs. For example: Federally incorporat-\ned non-profits must send their members a copy or a summary of all the financial \ndocuments they are required to present at the annual meeting. If a summary is \nprovided, the non-profit must indicate how members can obtain a full copy at no \ncost. To lessen this burdensome obligation, your organization can instead provide \nin its by-laws to notify its members, according to the same rules for notification \nas for general meetings, that these documents are available at your head office \nand that members are free to receive a copy at no charge either by visiting the \noffice in person or by prepaid mail.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1476, "end_char_idx": 2363, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "433abf83-d941-4f6b-a2f9-95f1ef45c91d": {"__data__": {"id_": "433abf83-d941-4f6b-a2f9-95f1ef45c91d", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section discusses the requirements for presenting financial information at annual general meetings (AGMs) for federally incorporated organizations. It mentions that financial statements must be approved and signed, and if applicable, accompanied by a public accountant's report. It also outlines specific requirements for federally incorporated non-profits, such as sending members copies or summaries of financial documents and providing access to full copies at no cost. Additionally, it suggests ways to streamline this process, such as notifying members that documents are available at the organization's head office for free.", "next_section_summary": "This section outlines the categories of federally incorporated non-profits based on their soliciting status and gross annual revenue. It also discusses the requirements for naming a public accountant and the intensity of review by the accountant based on revenue thresholds. Additionally, it touches on board elections and the length of director terms, highlighting the option to have longer terms specified in the organization's bylaws.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the level of scrutiny required for federally incorporated non-profits based on their gross annual income and whether they are considered a \"soliciting corporation\". It outlines the requirements for different categories of non-profits in terms of naming a public accountant and the intensity of review by the accountant. The section also mentions the definition of \"public sources\" and directs readers to Corporations Canada's website for more information. Key entities mentioned include federally incorporated non-profits, public accountants, and Corporations Canada.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the specific requirements for federally incorporated non-profits in terms of naming a public accountant and the intensity of review by the accountant based on their gross annual revenue and soliciting status?\n2. How does the level of scrutiny required for federally incorporated non-profits vary based on their gross annual income and whether they are considered a \"soliciting corporation\"?\n3. What options do members of federally incorporated non-profits have in terms of choosing between a review engagement and an audit by a public accountant, depending on the organization's gross annual revenue and soliciting status?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "7bf252ee-0804-439c-bd5c-c4af7eb9683b", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "dd5429b443065aefda6a1d