 covers the default one-year term, the option to have longer terms and staggered elections, maximum term lengths for provincially and federally incorporated organizations, and the possibility of setting term limits for directors. It also mentions the process for re-election and retirement of directors at annual general meetings.", "section_summary": "This section covers the requirements and options for financial audits or review engagements based on the organization's annual revenue, as well as guidelines for board elections including the length of terms for directors. It also mentions the importance of staggering terms to have a mix of experienced and new directors on the board. The section provides information on how to establish staggered terms in the organization's bylaws and the maximum term lengths allowed for provincially and federally incorporated non-profits.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the options for financial audits or review engagements based on an organization's annual revenue, and what are the specific thresholds that determine whether an audit is mandatory or optional?\n2. How can non-profit organizations establish staggered terms for directors through their bylaws, and what are the maximum term lengths allowed for provincially and federally incorporated non-profits?\n3. What is the default length of term for directors in non-profit organizations, and how can organizations provide for longer terms in their bylaws to ensure a mix of experienced and new directors on the board?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "7bf252ee-0804-439c-bd5c-c4af7eb9683b", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "dd5429b443065aefda6a1d1bb4669ab4207425f9990f5356f7cf225ef0b3d66a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "55aabf50-2db9-442d-b9a1-3bad13f54918", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "d00f257aa6d0cee656a5de33f8fcb74ea0e21fd8e39f95f3c6523d2ab8266bb7", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "62368369-8298-4ab4-805c-bf687399a535", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "deaab75bd116e3fcf4b84c031a0664aecb5c0c57c5a7cb77bb9b766f20732c2d", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "k\nNo An audit by default, but members \ncan opt for a review engagement \nby special resolution\nYes > $ 250 k No An audit is mandatory\nNo < $ 1 M Yes, in which case there will \nbe no review (i.e. a compi-\nlation)\nReview engagement by default. \nbut members can require an \naudit by ordinary resolution\nNo > $ 1 M No An audit is mandatory\n12  Board elections\nLength of term. Directors are, by default, elected for one-year terms at every AGM, but providing \nfor longer terms in your bylaws allows the terms to be staggered so that the organization has both expe-\nrienced and fresh directors working alongside one another. To establish this system, directors are initially \nelected for unequal term lengths. For provincially incorporated organizations, the maximum term length \nthat by-laws can validly establish is two years; it is four years for federally incorporated non-profits. If, in \na federally incorporated nonprofit, a director is elected for a term whose length is not expressly stated, it", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 867, "end_char_idx": 1863, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "62368369-8298-4ab4-805c-bf687399a535": {"__data__": {"id_": "62368369-8298-4ab4-805c-bf687399a535", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "This section covers the requirements and options for financial audits or review engagements based on the organization's annual revenue, as well as guidelines for board elections including the length of terms for directors. It also mentions the importance of staggering terms to have a mix of experienced and new directors on the board. The section provides information on how to establish staggered terms in the organization's bylaws and the maximum term lengths allowed for provincially and federally incorporated non-profits.", "next_section_summary": "The section discusses the election and term limits for directors in federally and provincially incorporated non-profit organizations. It explains that in federally incorporated non-profits, a director's term ends at the close of the following AGM if the length of the term is not specified. For provincially incorporated non-profits, directors must retire yearly but can be eligible for re-election. The section also mentions that directors can be re-elected indefinitely unless term limits are set in the organization's by-laws.", "section_summary": "The section discusses the election and terms of directors in non-profit organizations. It covers the default one-year term, the option to have longer terms and staggered elections, maximum term lengths for provincially and federally incorporated organizations, and the possibility of setting term limits for directors. It also mentions the process for re-election and retirement of directors at annual general meetings.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the maximum term lengths that can be established in the bylaws for directors in provincially and federally incorporated non-profit organizations?\n2. How can staggered terms for directors be established in non-profit organizations, and what are the benefits of having a mix of experienced and new directors on the board?\n3. Can directors in non-profit organizations be re-elected indefinitely, or are there term limits that can be set in the organization's bylaws to restrict re-election opportunities?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "7bf252ee-0804-439c-bd5c-c4af7eb9683b", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "dd5429b443065aefda6a1d1bb4669ab4207425f9990f5356f7cf225ef0b3d66a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "97b0d192-5c95-4986-99f1-62484d5e4a7c", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "ad459cdd4102f69949ef17ef8ad894caf2e0de54e884f458210dc440dd9552eb", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "9d0644fc-ee2b-4249-b7af-de5af7b8fd5c", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "333b466adbd73b5b8d23b1acac910208b6e767fcf0a0d6f759e4b40ffe954b95", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "term. Directors are, by default, elected for one-year terms at every AGM, but providing \nfor longer terms in your bylaws allows the terms to be staggered so that the organization has both expe-\nrienced and fresh directors working alongside one another. To establish this system, directors are initially \nelected for unequal term lengths. For provincially incorporated organizations, the maximum term length \nthat by-laws can validly establish is two years; it is four years for federally incorporated non-profits. If, in \na federally incorporated nonprofit, a director is elected for a term whose length is not expressly stated, it \nends with the close of the following AGM. Similarly, for provincially incorporated non-profits, the election \n\u201cshall take place yearly, and all the directors then in office shall retire, but, if otherwise qualified, they shall \nbe eligible for reelection.\u201d\nTerm limits. Directors can be re-elected indefinitely, unless the by-laws set term limits, which organi-\nzations often choose to impose. Sometimes these limits allow a director to be re-elected only after the", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1232, "end_char_idx": 2330, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "9d0644fc-ee2b-4249-b7af-de5af7b8fd5c": {"__data__": {"id_": "9d0644fc-ee2b-4249-b7af-de5af7b8fd5c", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The section discusses the election and terms of directors in non-profit organizations. It covers the default one-year term, the option to have longer terms and staggered elections, maximum term lengths for provincially and federally incorporated organizations, and the possibility of setting term limits for directors. It also mentions the process for re-election and retirement of directors at annual general meetings.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the eligibility requirements for directors, including being at least 18 years old, not currently bankrupt, and not having certain intellectual disabilities. It also mentions that directors must be \"natural persons\" and cannot be incorporated organizations. However, exceptions are made for individuals under 18 years old and those with intellectual disabilities to be directors of non-profits that concern them. The section also touches on the number of board members required, based on the organization's constitution or articles of incorporation for federally incorporated non-profits.", "section_summary": "The section discusses the election and term limits for directors in federally and provincially incorporated non-profit organizations. It explains that in federally incorporated non-profits, a director's term ends at the close of the following AGM if the length of the term is not specified. For provincially incorporated non-profits, directors must retire yearly but can be eligible for re-election. The section also mentions that directors can be re-elected indefinitely unless term limits are set in the organization's by-laws.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the default term limits for directors in federally incorporated non-profit organizations if the length of the term is not specified?\n2. In provincially incorporated non-profits, how often do directors have to retire and when are they eligible for re-election?\n3. How do term limits for directors in non-profit organizations typically work, and what factors may influence whether term limits are set in an organization's by-laws?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "7bf252ee-0804-439c-bd5c-c4af7eb9683b", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "dd5429b443065aefda6a1d1bb4669ab4207425f9990f5356f7cf225ef0b3d66a", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "62368369-8298-4ab4-805c-bf687399a535", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "17", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "f43c9f6c8f6293436cea54ed9ea7923a29e1a32ae1ac1a0ac53f8dfa0edf733e", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "for federally incorporated non-profits. If, in \na federally incorporated nonprofit, a director is elected for a term whose length is not expressly stated, it \nends with the close of the following AGM. Similarly, for provincially incorporated non-profits, the election \n\u201cshall take place yearly, and all the directors then in office shall retire, but, if otherwise qualified, they shall \nbe eligible for reelection.\u201d\nTerm limits. Directors can be re-elected indefinitely, unless the by-laws set term limits, which organi-\nzations often choose to impose. Sometimes these limits allow a director to be re-elected only after the end \nof a period that begins at the end of their term.", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1706, "end_char_idx": 2385, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "985eb033-290a-4c81-b79a-7eedf3466906": {"__data__": {"id_": "985eb033-290a-4c81-b79a-7eedf3466906", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The section discusses the election and term limits for directors in federally and provincially incorporated non-profit organizations. It explains that in federally incorporated non-profits, a director's term ends at the close of the following AGM if the length of the term is not specified. For provincially incorporated non-profits, directors must retire yearly but can be eligible for re-election. The section also mentions that directors can be re-elected indefinitely unless term limits are set in the organization's by-laws.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the requirements and considerations related to the board of directors of non-profit organizations. Key topics include the qualifications and restrictions for directors, the number of board members required, and the differences between federally and provincially incorporated non-profits in terms of board size regulations. The section also mentions the importance of checking the organization's by-laws and constitution for any additional restrictions on board membership.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the eligibility requirements for directors, including being at least 18 years old, not currently bankrupt, and not having certain intellectual disabilities. It also 