 the organization, and the AGM (Annual General Meeting).", "section_summary": "The key topics of the section include the size of the board of directors for provincially incorporated non-profits, the process for changing the number of seats on the board, the strategy of choosing an odd number of directors to avoid tie votes, the possibility of reserving seats for specific categories of people on the board, and the voting process for elections of directors. The section also mentions the ability of the board to fill vacancies that arise during the year. Key entities mentioned include provincially incorporated non-profits, the Registraire des entreprises, and the board of directors.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How can provincially incorporated non-profits change the number of seats on their board of directors, and what is the process they need to follow to do so?\n2. What strategy is commonly used to avoid tie votes when electing directors for provincially incorporated non-profits, and why is it recommended?\n3. In what circumstances can vacancies on the board of directors of provincially incorporated non-profits be filled by the board itself, and what is the process for doing so?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "ac5bfc30-5f3c-4e63-b0a4-076f4ecb92e5", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "61b06dedf2f2382418f022542ee256d90838b2bda94a54f00ed6c954ebc5c258", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "0cc78c02-616b-40bb-b93e-1721ce0c73d5", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "40a2cb1f283926439b1c7917ee21fa33d35c49acc3bfe22b3b9515a022f3bc43", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "8c7c3774-7205-4067-941d-7096ce15dc9a", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "3aff135baeb594c3552158fe645d6869c8ee8009320ca1c911e3cb311489bbc0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "one \nis enough. Provincially incorporated non-profits can't establish a range: the size of the board is always a \nspecific number. A general meeting resolution on its own is also not enough, for a provincially incorporated \norganization, to change the number of seats: it also needs to send notice of the change to the Registraire \ndes entreprises using the proper form. Choosing an odd number of directors is a strategy used to try to \navoid the chance of tie votes.\nReserved seats. It is also possible for the by-laws to reserve a certain number or proportion of seats \non the board of directors for particular categories of people, such as people who benefit from the organiza-\ntion\u2019s services or are active volunteers.\nVoting. Elections of directors of provincially incorporated non-profits must be by ballot, although any \nvacancies that arise during the year can be filled for the rest of that director\u2019s term by the board itself. As \nlong as the board retains quorum, it can fill vacancies even if no directors originally elected by the mem-\nbers remain. But the board", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1412, "end_char_idx": 2487, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "8c7c3774-7205-4067-941d-7096ce15dc9a": {"__data__": {"id_": "8c7c3774-7205-4067-941d-7096ce15dc9a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of the section include the size of the board of directors for provincially incorporated non-profits, the process for changing the number of seats on the board, the strategy of choosing an odd number of directors to avoid tie votes, the possibility of reserving seats for specific categories of people on the board, and the voting process for elections of directors. The section also mentions the ability of the board to fill vacancies that arise during the year. Key entities mentioned include provincially incorporated non-profits, the Registraire des entreprises, and the board of directors.", "next_section_summary": "This section discusses the process of filling vacancies on a board of directors, the importance of holding elections at an AGM, and the rules for removing board members. It emphasizes the need for quorum to fill vacancies, the requirement to hold elections at AGMs, and the necessity of outlining removal procedures in the by-laws or letters patent. The section also references additional information on holding Special General Meetings and the incorporation of non-profits in Quebec.", "section_summary": "The key topics of this section include tie votes, reserved seats on the board of directors, voting procedures for elections, filling vacancies on the board, holding elections at the AGM, and removing board members. The entities mentioned are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the AGM (Annual General Meeting).", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. What are the rules for filling vacancies on a board of directors for provincially incorporated non-profits, and how does the process differ for elections held at an Annual General Meeting (AGM) versus vacancies that arise during the year?\n2. How can by-laws reserve seats on the board of directors for specific categories of people, and what are some examples of categories that may be reserved for these seats?\n3. In the event that an election is not held at an AGM as required, what is the protocol for ensuring that the existing directors remain in their positions until a general meeting is called and elections are held?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "ac5bfc30-5f3c-4e63-b0a4-076f4ecb92e5", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "61b06dedf2f2382418f022542ee256d90838b2bda94a54f00ed6c954ebc5c258", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "0b15bde9-60e8-40ac-8bf4-f9814db5cc99", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "d7e2289704b315841fc3f6690502f4c381eddb308df4fb957a5dceb67a2a03f0", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "3": {"node_id": "eed4f553-c0c2-466d-9e68-d7e52a4a5002", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {}, "hash": "d8c88acf9fb9ef92347de06aa0618532d465a15db2b4a0dbc0f1514423279d0e", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "tie votes.\nReserved seats. It is also possible for the by-laws to reserve a certain number or proportion of seats \non the board of directors for particular categories of people, such as people who benefit from the organiza-\ntion\u2019s services or are active volunteers.\nVoting. Elections of directors of provincially incorporated non-profits must be by ballot, although any \nvacancies that arise during the year can be filled for the rest of that director\u2019s term by the board itself. As \nlong as the board retains quorum, it can fill vacancies even if no directors originally elected by the mem-\nbers remain. But the board can never extend a director\u2019s mandate beyond the one the members initially \nelected them to.\nIf no election is held. If, for whatever reason, an election is not held at your AGM as it should be, \nyour existing directors remain in their positions until a general meeting is called and elections held. This \nensures that even if your AGM doesn\u2019t happen, you\u2019re not left without a board of directors.\nRemoving board members. The rules describing how to remove", "mimetype": "text/plain", "start_char_idx": 1869, "end_char_idx": 2944, "metadata_seperator": "\n", "text_template": "[Excerpt from document]\n{metadata_str}\nExcerpt:\n-----\n{content}\n-----\n", "class_name": "TextNode"}, "__type__": "1"}, "eed4f553-c0c2-466d-9e68-d7e52a4a5002": {"__data__": {"id_": "eed4f553-c0c2-466d-9e68-d7e52a4a5002", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16", "prev_section_summary": "The key topics of this section include tie votes, reserved seats on the board of directors, voting procedures for elections, filling vacancies on the board, holding elections at the AGM, and removing board members. The entities mentioned are the board of directors, members of the organization, and the AGM (Annual General Meeting).", "next_section_summary": "This section provides further resources and legal notices related to non-profit governance. It includes information on resources available for administrators and members of associations, as well as a guide on the rights, duties, and responsibilities of administrators of non-profit organizations. The resources mentioned are primarily in French and can be borrowed from COCo's resource library or purchased from them. The section also mentions a toolbox on democratic governance for non-profit organizations in community action.", "section_summary": "This section discusses the process of filling vacancies on a board of directors, the importance of holding elections at an AGM, and the rules for removing board members. It emphasizes the need for quorum to fill vacancies, the requirement to hold elections at AGMs, and the necessity of outlining removal procedures in the by-laws or letters patent. The section also references additional information on holding Special General Meetings and the incorporation of non-profits in Quebec.", "questions_this_excerpt_can_answer": "1. How can a board of directors fill vacancies even if no directors originally elected by the members remain, as long as quorum is retained?\n2. What happens if an election is not held at an Annual General Meeting (AGM) for a non-profit organization, and how can existing directors remain in their positions until elections are held?\n3. What are the rules and procedures for removing a board member from a provincially incorporated non-profit organization, and where can additional information on this topic be found in the document?"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": ["file_name", "file_type", "file_size", "creation_date", "last_modified_date", "last_accessed_date"], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "ac5bfc30-5f3c-4e63-b0a4-076f4ecb92e5", "node_type": "4", "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "61b06dedf2f2382418f022542ee256d90838b2bda94a54f00ed6c954ebc5c258", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}, "2": {"node_id": "8c7c3774-7205-4067-941d-7096ce15dc9a", "node_type": "1", "metadata": {"page_label": "18", "file_name": "AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_path": "data\\dev\\docs\\AGM-Legal-Info-Sheet-EN-2019.pdf", "file_type": "application/pdf", "file_size": 432341, "creation_date": "2025-02-16", "last_modified_date": "2025-02-16"}, "hash": "ad3d8afba5f41ff35a65a043f6b870c032cd95e8dcee139a1c2a6849d6ff7aa5", "class_name": "RelatedNodeInfo"}}, "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_separator": "\n", "text": "As \nlong as the board retains quorum, it can fill vacancies even if no directors originally elected by the mem-\nbers remain. But the board can never extend a director\u2019s mandate beyond the one the members initially \nelected them to.\nIf no election is held. If, for whatever reason, an election is not held at your AGM as it should be, \nyour existing directors remain in their positions until a general meeting is called and elections held. This \nensures that even if your AGM doesn\u2019t happen, you\u2019re not left without a board of directors.\nRemoving board members. The rules describing how to remove a board member have to be \noutlined in the by-laws and even this may not be enough for a provincially incorporated non-profit, where \nthey may have to be written in your letters patent. \nSee more on this topic above in Section 4 \u2013 When to have a Special General Meeting (SGM), or in COCo\u2019s \ninfos